-- Finmeccanica, Fincantieri May Get $7 Billion in Brazil Orders, Sole Says
-- Sonia Sirletti
-- 2010-06-29T06:28:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/finmeccanica-fincantieri-may-get-7-billion-in-brazil-orders-sole-says.html

          
          
             Finmeccanica SpA  and Fincantieri SpA
may get Brazilian contracts worth more than 6 billion euros
($7.4 billion),  Il Sole 24 Ore  reported, without saying where it
got the information.  
 The orders, related to shipbuilding infrastructure and
satellite systems, may be agreed upon during a visit by Italian
Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi , who arrived in Brazil
yesterday, the Italian newspaper said.  
 Italian companies may sign contracts in Brazil for about 10
billion euros during the prime ministerâ€™s visit, Sole said.  
